Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • Session
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class Session
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is an entity class to store related information about sessions/classes (Lecture, Tutorial, Laboratory). The Session objects are stored in an ArrayList under a Course object.
    See Also:

        public Session​(java.lang.String type,
               java.lang.String group,
               java.lang.String dayTime,
               java.lang.String location,
               java.lang.String tutorName,
               int maxCapacity,
               int numberRegistered)
        Constructor for Session object, instantiating the below attributes
        Parameters:
        type - String type of session (LEC, TUT or LAB for Lecture, Tutorial and Lab).
        group - String group ID of the session (CE1, SE3, etc).
        dayTime - String timing for the session, following "Day of the week HH:MM - HH:MM" format.
        location - String describing the venue for the session.
        tutorName - String containing tutor name for that session.
        maxCapacity - int vacancy of the session (number of students it can accomodate at the moment).
        numberRegistered - int describing number of student currently registered.

        public boolean deregisterStudent​(Student student)
        A method to deregister Student from the calling session. This method utilise the ArrayList remove method to deregister the Student from studentList ArrayList
        Parameters:
        student - Student object to be deregistered (removed) from the calling session.
        Returns:
        false if the process failed. Return true if the student is successfully removed from the student list of the session.
        See Also:
        ArrayList

      • addStudent

        public int addStudent​(Student student)

        Parameters:
        student - Student student object to be added into this session
        Returns:
